            <span class="hljs-tag">&lt;/<span class="hljs-title">a</span>&gt;</span></pre>
            <h2 class="cd-text cd-title">Grouped health badges</h2>
            <p class="cd-text">When two or more health badges are next to each other, they overlap slightly. There should be a maximum of 3 health badges per product.</p>
            <a href="health-badges#0" class="health-badge health-badge--fibre-uk">
                <span class="sr-only">high in fibre</span>
            </a>
            <a href="health-badges#0" class="health-badge health-badge--vitamins">
                <span class="sr-only">A source of at least two vitamins and minerals</span>
            </a>
            <a href="health-badges#0" class="health-badge health-badge--protein">
                <span class="sr-only">A source of protein</span>
            </a>

            <h2 class="cd-text cd-title">Usage without links</h2>
            <p class="cd-text">Ideally health badges would be used as a navigation aid and on click would filter by health badge or direct users to a page that collects all products that contain that health badge. If this is not possible, use of a <code>div</code> element is appropriate.</p>

            <p>
                <div class="health-badge health-badge--calories">
                    <span aria-hidden="true">130</span>
                    <span class="sr-only">only 130 calories</span>
                </div>
            </p>
<pre class="hljs xml margin-reset"><span class="hljs-tag">&lt;<span class="hljs-title">div</span> <span class="hljs-attribute">class</span>=<span class="hljs-value">"health-badge health-badge--calories"</span>&gt;</span>
    <span class="hljs-tag">&lt;<span class="hljs-title">span</span> <span class="hljs-attribute">aria-hidden</span>=<span class="hljs-value">"true"</span>&gt;</span>130<span class="hljs-tag">&lt;/<span class="hljs-title">span</span>&gt;</span>
    <span class="hljs-tag">&lt;<span class="hljs-title">span</span> <span class="hljs-attribute">class</span>=<span class="hljs-value">"sr-only"</span>&gt;</span>only 130 calories<span class="hljs-tag">&lt;/<span class="hljs-title">span</span>&gt;</span>
<span class="hljs-tag">&lt;/<span class="hljs-title">div</span>&gt;</span></pre>        </div>
    </div>
